JOHANNESBURG Two trains collided head-on on Monday at the Lynross station between Medunsa and Rosslyn on Monday.Gauteng Metrorail spokesperson Lillian Mofokeng confirmed the collision. More than 100 people have been injured after two trains collided on the same track when they were travelling from different directions, said Mofokeng.She said there were no fatalities.Mofokeng added that passengers were being transported with buses.READ: Metrorail train set on fire in CenturionEarlier, Tshwane emergency services spokesperson Johan Pieterse said about 100 patients were injured and about 20 were seriously injured.Pieterse said the collision happened around 6pm.eNCA